comments: Theis (BOS) sets the screen on Holiday (MIL) and absorbs the contact.
Holiday (MIL) and Theis (BOS) engage and disengage with one another after Theis begins rolling toward the lane.
Connaughton (MIL) firms up in his screening position in Smart's (BOS) path and absorbs the contact by collapsing his arms. Smart's reaction is not consistent with the amount of contact.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) goes to, not through, Theis' (BOS) space and spins off of the contact made inside the lane.
As Theis (BOS) falls to the floor, he makes marginal contact with Antetokounmpo (MIL).
Middleton's (MIL) arm is extended slightly forward and marginal contact occurs with Brown's (BOS) left arm as he makes the pass.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) is in the lane for longer than three seconds without actively guarding an opponent.
Connaughton (MIL) legally contests the shot attempt by Tatum (BOS).
Brown (BOS) and Antetokounmpo (MIL) engage and disengage with one another following the pick.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) places his left arm against Tatum (BOS) during his driving shot attempt but the contact is marginal.
Teague (BOS) makes contact with the ball and the part of DiVincenzo's (MIL) hand that is on the ball during the driving shot attempt.
Middleton (MIL) briefly has his arms around Theis' (BOS) upper half before correcting.
Theis (BOS) makes marginal contact with Middleton (MIL) during the screen.
Theis (BOS) firms up in his screening position in Middleton's (MIL) path and absorbs the contact.
Lopez (MIL) establishes himself in a screening position in Brown's (BOS) path and does not deliver the contact.
Theis (BOS) establishes himself in a screening position in Middleton's (MIL) path and does not deliver the contact.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) extends into Brown's (BOS) path as Brown attempts to avoid the contact.
Theis (BOS) establishes himself in a screening position in Middleton's (MIL) path and does not deliver the contact.
Theis (BOS) steps into the lane before Antetokounmpo (MIL) releases the free throw.

Thompson (BOS) and Antetokounmpo (MIL) both make a legal attempt to reach the inbound pass, and the contact should have been deemed incidental.  Referees reviewed the call in instant replay as per the automatic trigger for fouls called at when there is no time remaining on the clock at the end of any period to confirm that the foul was called before the expiration of time, but the foul itself is not a reviewable matter.
